  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Master",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description &amp; Requirements</strong></p>\n<p>Ship management and marine logistics company is looking for a committed person to join the team:</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p>\n<p>As a Master you will be responsible for the safe and efficient operation of the vessel and its crew in order to achieve the desired commercial and operational objectives.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>You will prepare the voyages and the projects, and you will ensure that the vessel is manoeuvred and navigated safely and efficiently.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>You will manage the crew so they know their responsibilities and are able to perform them to the best of their abilities.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>You will create a good atmosphere, and strive for harmony, order and cleanliness on board to ensure that a hygienic and pleasant working environment is achieved.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<p>· Hold at least a Class 2 CoC or higher</p>\n<p>· Experience in Tanker vessel</p>\n<p>· Team player</p>\n<p>· High level of English and Bahasa Language competency required as you will need to communicate with our Indonesian crews and office staffs</p>\n<p>· Seafarer certificate required by MPA</p>\n<p>· Port Limit Special Grade Certificate</p>\n<p>· Port Limit Tanker Master Course Certificate</p>\n<p>· Pilotage Exemption (PELV) Certificate</p>\n<p><br></p>",
